# Naming Rules

## Variables & Parameters
- `FREQ_EXC`, `FREQ_INH` — background firing rates (Hz). ALL_CAPS = simulation-level constants.
- `SIMU_DURATION`, `STIM_DURATION` — durations (ms). ALL_CAPS in CLI / build_cell scope.
- `initW`, `fixedW` — synaptic weight params (µS). camelCase is legacy; keep as-is.
- `syn_pos_seed`, `bg_spike_gen_seed`, `clus_spike_gen_seed` — three orthogonal seeds. Never rename.
- `sec_syn_bg_exc_df` — filtered DataFrame slice: `sec`=section, `syn`=synapse, `bg`=background, `exc`=excitatory.
- `spk_rnd`, `loc_rnd`, `clus_loc_rnd` — RNG instances. Prefix indicates purpose (spike / location / cluster-location).

## DataFrame Columns (`section_synapse_df`)
- `type`: `'A'` = excitatory, `'B'` = inhibitory. Single-char legacy codes; do not change.
- `cluster_flag`: `-1` = background, `1` = cluster member.
- `cluster_center_flag`: `1` = center, `0` = surround, `-1` = non-cluster.
- `syn_w`: weight in **nS** (not µS). Conversion: `syn_w = 1000 * initW_distr`.
- `spike_train`: list of lists — clustered stimulus spike times per activation level.
- `spike_train_bg`: list of lists — background spike times per trial.

## Functions
- `add_background_exc_inputs()` / `add_background_inh_inputs()` — background pipeline.
- `add_clustered_inputs()` — cluster stimulus injection.
- `_func()` prefix — internal / replay variant (e.g. `_add_background_exc_inputs_replay`).
- `generate_*` — pure data generation, no NEURON side effects.
- `row_syn_key()` — unique synapse identifier for replay matching.

## File & Folder Naming
- Output folder: `{sec_type}_range{dis_to_root}_{spat}_{simu}{suffix}_expected/{tag}/{epoch}`
- Arrays: `soma_v_array.npy`, `dend_nmda_i_array.npy`, etc. — snake_case + `_array` suffix.
- CSV: `section_synapse_df.csv` — exact name, downstream scripts depend on it.

## Abbreviations (see also docs/CONVENTIONS.md)
- `exc` = excitatory, `inh` = inhibitory, `bg` = background
- `syn` = synapse, `sec` = section, `seg` = segment
- `clus` = clustered, `distr` = distributed
- `ctr` = center, `suc` = successor, `pre` = predecessor
- `aff` = afferent fiber, `perm` = permutation
